As we approach the 2023 general election, The available report has shown that some political players have already started indicating interest in the position the will be contesting for in 2023.
In regard to this, there are indication that the wife of the executive governor of Anambra state, Mrs. Ebelechukwu Obiano may likely contest for Anambra North Senatorial District in the 2023 general elections.
According to the report, Governor Willie Obiano of Anambra State disclosed that his wife, Mrs. Ebelechukwu Obiano, will contest for Anambra North Senatorial District in the 2023 general elections.
Obiano states this while addressing members of Nigeria Union Journalists (NUJ), Anambra State chapter, at his home town, Aguleri, in Anambra East Local Government Area of the state, shortly after embarking on tour with members of NUJ to Anambra International Conference Centre (AICC) with 10,000 capacity, Awka City Stadium and the State International Passenger/Cargo Airport.
He said that his wife is contesting for the position in order to continue from her humanitarian services to the people of the state.
With this, it’s now clear that the wife of the executive governor of Anambra state, Mrs. Ebelechukwu Obiano is already working behind the scene in order to ensure that he contest for Anambra North Senatorial District in the 2023 general elections.


